<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="29.[189,533,684,711]" box="[189,533,684,711]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,533,684,711]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,533,684,711]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Distribution and phenology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[189,1399,731,793]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Arunachal-Pradesh and Assam; also in 
<collectingCountry box="[644,762,732,758]" name="Myanmar" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
; 
<quantity box="[773,924,731,758]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" unit="m" value="700.0" valueMax="1100.0" valueMin="300.0">300–1100 m</quantity>
. Flowering: February to March; fruiting: February to April.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[189,437,832,858]" box="[189,437,832,858]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,437,832,858]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,437,832,858]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Conservation status</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[189,1398,877,940]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Least Concern. 
<taxonomicName box="[382,586,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="burkillii">
<emphasis box="[382,586,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Begonia burkillii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an EOO of 
<quantity box="[795,924,878,905]" metricMagnitude="7" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.34" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" unit="km" value="83400.0">83,400 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[925,934,877,891]" fontSize="6" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">2</superScript>
and an AOO of 
<quantity box="[1147,1225,878,905]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.2" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" unit="km" value="72.0">72 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="right" box="[1226,1235,877,891]" fontSize="6" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">2</superScript>
, with a wide distribution through undisturbed forest in Arunachal-Pradesh and into Northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1126,1242,914,940]" name="Myanmar" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[189,303,979,1005]" box="[189,303,979,1005]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,979,1005]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,979,1005]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[189,1399,1025,1193]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Specimens from the region lacked female flowers, which are described based on the protologue and photographs of cultivated plants. The leaf markings can vary in colour from red to purple-brown to almost black, but keep the same pattern (
<figureCitation box="[682,770,1096,1122]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="27.[189,232,1958,1984]" captionTargetBox="[415,1173,265,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[415,1173,265,1921]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Fig. 17. Begonia burkillii Dunn. A. Leaf pattern. B. Male flowers. Photograph A courtesy of Aaron Matsumoto and photograph B courtesy of Earl I-Lan of plants in cultivation in private collections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3787075" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3787075/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). This species is perhaps most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Irmsch. (Irmscher" authorityYear="1921" box="[1268,1398,1096,1122]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="handelii">
<emphasis box="[1268,1398,1096,1122]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">B. handelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in being rhizomatous and having 4-locular fruit, but that species has large rounded outer petals (not narrowly ovate), non-variegated leaves and fruit that is more pyramidal than rhomboid.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[189,1399,1232,1294]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
The lectotypification by 
<bibRefCitation author="Saikia R. &amp; Roy H. &amp; Borthakur S. K." box="[477,701,1232,1258]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="357 - 360" refId="ref57452" refString="Saikia R., Roy H. &amp; Borthakur S. K. 2011. New report of occurrence of two species of Begonia L. (Begoniaceae) from Assam, India. Pleione 5 (2): 357 - 360." type="journal article" year="2011">
Saikia 
<emphasis box="[557,616,1232,1258]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
(2011)
</bibRefCitation>
list two specimens (
<emphasis box="[943,1105,1232,1258]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Burkill 37706</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1162,1235,1232,1258]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">37121</emphasis>
) and hence is not valid. Here 
<emphasis box="[371,533,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Burkill 37139</emphasis>
(K) is designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[823,934,1267,1293]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
